('Ishav', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Shake vodka, Pisang and sour mix well with ice. Pour into a highball glass. Fill with soda water.', NULL),
('Imperial Cocktail', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Shake with ice and strain into cocktail glass.', NULL),
('Lemon Shot', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'Mix Galliano and Absolut Citron in a shot glass, lay lemon wedge sprinkled with sugar over glass and pour a rum over wedge and glass. light rum with a lighter and let burn for a second. Do shot quickly and suck on lemon. If it is done correctly, this will taste like a shot of sweet lemonade.', NULL),
('Sex on the Beach', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Half fill with cranberry juice and grapefruit juice, stir in highball glass.', NULL),
('Autodaf√©', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix and fill up with soda water. Drunk by finns on a sunny day any time of the year and day.', NULL),
('Gagliardo', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Shake well and serve in a cocktail glass. This is a home cocktail of American/Internet Bar del Pozzo, Pavia, Italy.', NULL),
('Surf City Lifesaver', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Lots of ice and soda top up in tall glass with cherry and a grin.', NULL),
('Grizzly Bear', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Served over ice. Sounds nasty, but tastes great.', NULL),
('Karsk', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Put a copper coin in a coffe-cup and fill up with coffee until you no longer see the coin, then add alcohol until you see the coin. Norwegian speciality.', NULL),
('Iced Coffee Fillip', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix together in a coffee mug and chill before serving.', NULL),
('Absinthe #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Steep wormwood in vodka for 48 hours. Remove, add the rest and steep for one week. Age.', NULL),
('Absinthe #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix together and let sit a few days. Strain through a coffee filter. To serve mix 1 part absinthe to 4 parts water, add ice, enjoy.', NULL),
('Amaretto Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine sugar and 3/4 cup water in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer until all sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and cool. In an aging container, combine apricot halves, almond extract, grain alcohol with 1/2 cup water, and brandy. Stir in cooled sugar syrup mixture. Cap and let age for 2 days. Remove apricot halves. (Save apricot halves, can be used', NULL),
('Angelica Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all herbs, nuts and spices with vodka in a 1 quart or larger aging container. Cap tightly and shake daily for 2 weeks. Strain through a fine muslin cloth or coffee filter, discarding solids. Clean out aging container. Place liquid back in container. Place sugar and water in saucepan and stir to combine over medium heat. When sugar is completely dissolved, set aside and let cool. When cool ', NULL),
('Caribbean Orange Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Pare very thinly the bright-colored rind from the oranges (no white). Blot the peel on paper towels to remove any excess oil. Put peel in a 4 cup screw-top jar. Add 2 cups vodka. Close jar. Store in a cool, dark place for 2 days or until the vodka has absorbed the flavor. Remove peel and add remaining vodka. Close jar and add remaining cup of vodka. Close the jar and store in a cool dark place at ', NULL),
('Coffee Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine coffee, sugar and water. Simmer 1 hour and let cool. Add vanilla and vodka. Age in sealed jar 2 to 3 weeks.', NULL),
('Cranberry Cordial', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Place the chopped cranberries in a 2 liter jar that has a tight-fitting lid. Add the sugar and rum. Adjust the lid securely and place the jar in a cool, dark place. Invert the jar and shake it every day for six weeks. Strain the cordial into bottles and seal with corks.', NULL),
('Cream Cordial', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In blender container, combine all ingredients, blend until smooth. Serve over ice if desired. Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to one month. Stir before using.', NULL),
('Creme de Menthe', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Bring sugar and water to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes. Cool. Add the remaining ingredients and stir. Cover and let ripen for 1 month.', NULL),
('Daiquiri Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Pare very thinly the bright-colored rind from the limes (no white). Blot the peel on paper towels to remove any excess oil. Put peel in a 4 cup screw-top jar. Add 2 cups of the rum. Close the jar. Store in a cool, dark place for 2 days or until rum has absorbed the flavor. Remove the peel and add the sugar. Shake vigorously until the sugar dissolves and add remaining cup of rum. Close jar and stor', NULL),
('Fresh Mint Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Wash leaves in cold water several times. Shake or pat dry gently. Snip each leaf in half or thirds. Discard stems. measure cut mint leaves, packing lightly. Combine mint leaves and vodka in aging container. Cap and let stand in a cool place for 2 weeks, shaking occasionally. After initial aging, strain leaves from liqueur, discard leaves. In a sucepan, combine sugar and water. Bring to a boil, sti', NULL),
('Galliano', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Boil water, corn syrup and sugar for 5 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients and stir. Cover and let stand 1 month.', NULL),
('Grand Orange-Cognac Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Place zest and sugar in a small bowl. Mash and mix together with the back of a wooden spoon or a pestle. Continue mashing until sugar is absorbed into the orange zest and is no longer distinct. Place into aging container. Add cognac. Stir, cap and let age in a cool dark place 2 to 3 months, shaking monthly. After initial aging, pour through fine mesh strainer placed over medium bowl. Rinse out agi', NULL),
('Honey Liquor', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Dissolve honey in hot water. The water should not be hotter than 45 degrees Celsius. Let the mixture cool down, then add spirit of wine.', NULL),
('Irish Cream', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix scotch and milk. Add half-and-half. Add rest.', NULL),
('Irish Cream Liqueur #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all ingredients in a blender until smooth. Store in the refrigerator for up to one month.', NULL),
('Irish Cream Liqueur #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Place all ingredients in a blender, blend well. Bottle and let mellow in refrigerator at least one week befor serving. this has been found to be best after 1-2 weeks. Store in refrigerator. Liqueur at room temperature by removing form refrigerator 1-2 hours before serving.', NULL),
('Irish Cream Liqueur #3', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Blend (use blender) all ingredients until smooth. Store tightly covered in refrigerator. Shake before serving. Keeps up to one month.', NULL),
('Kahlua #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. let cool and add vanilla and either a pint or fifth of Vodka. Drink and Enjoy!!', NULL),
('Kahlua #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Simmer water, sugar, and coffee until the sugar dissolves. Put vanilla bean and bourbon in a gallon jug and add the coffee syrup you just prepared. Cover and let sit one month.', NULL),
('Kahlua #4', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix first 4 ingredients and simmer them for 1.5-2 hours with occasional stirring. Cool. Add the rest of the stuff. Filter and pour into dark bottles. Keep the bottles in a cool, dark place for 3 months. Shake every day.', NULL),
('Medd', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Spread the yeast on a piece of bread. Boil the water, honey and sugar. Stand in an earthenware pot. Skim off anyscum. Add lemon juice, cloves and ginger. Leave to cool. When just warm, float the bread and yeast on the top. Cover with a clean cloth. Leave for about 6-8 days. Strain and bottle. Corks should be loose to start with. Leave for at least 5-6 months.', NULL),
('Mexican Coffee Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Heat water in medium saucepan. when hot add coffee and stir until dissolved. Add sugar and vanilla bean, stirring well to combine. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Imediately reduce heat so that a very low boil is maintained for one minute. Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm. Pour vodka and brandy into aging container. Add the cooled coffee mixture and the chocolate extract. Stir well. Cap a', NULL),
('Pineapple Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Crush pineapple pieces *very* finely. Put together with the pineapple juice in a pan, add the sugar. Leave to stand over night. Drain syrup and strain pineapple pieces through a cheese cloth or in a food processor. Mix juice with rum and vodka, add lemon juice to taste. Pour in a 0.7 l bottle and fill to the brim with pineapple juice or water. Leave at least one week.', NULL),
('Plum Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Wash plums and pat dry. Cut plums in half or smaller, pit. Place plums in aging container. Pour sugar over plums, stir. Add vodka and brandy stirring to partly disolve sugar. Cap container and place in a cool, dark place for 2 months, stir occasionally. Place a strainer over large bowl and strain liqueur. Press liquid from plums with the back of a wooden spoon. Discard plum pulp. Re-strain liqueur', NULL),
('Scottish Highland Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all ingreds in aging container. Cover tightly and shake gently several times during the first 24 hrs. After 24 hrs, remove the lemon zest. Cover again and let stand in a cool, dark place for 2 weeks, shaking gently every other day. Strain through a wire sieve to remove the angelica root and fennel. Return to aging container, cover and let stand undisturbed in a cool dark place for 6 months', NULL),
('Tia-Maria', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Boil water, sugar and coffe for 10 mins and let cool. Add rum and vanilla. Put in clean bottle(s) and leave for 1 week before using.', NULL),
('Vanilla-Coffee Liqueur', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine sugars and water. Boil for 5 minutes. Gradually stir in coffee. Cool. Add vodka and vanilla and mix thoroughly. Cover and let ripen for 1 month. Remove vanilla bean.', 'vanilla_coffee_liqueur.jpg'),
('Voodoo Juice', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Pour over ice in a hurricane class. Float dark rum on top and serve.', NULL),
('Artillery Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all the ingredients in a large punch bowl with a block of ice. If found too dry, sugar syrup may be added. Decorate with twists of lemon peel.', NULL),
('Berry Deadly', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Add all ingredients to large bowl. Stir gently. Serve chilled.', NULL),
('Boo Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine Orange Kool-Aid and Vodka. Add some J√§germeister and it will look and taste scary.', NULL),
('Champagne Punch #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all of the ingredients and serve in punch cups.', NULL),
('Champagne Punch #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix sugar, brandy and 5 bottles champagne in a punch bowl. Then stir in orange, lemon and lime sliced thin into rounds, pineapple chunks and ice. Stir until well mixed. To complete, garnish with strawberries and pour a final bottle of champagne theatrically over the top.', NULL),
('Cold Duck Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix all liquids in a large punch bowl. Float the sherbet on top.', NULL),
('Egg Nog - Kahlua', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix kahlua with eggnog in a wine glass and then sprinkle some nutmeg on top.', NULL),
('Egg Nog - Williamsburg', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Separate the eggs (yolk and white) Set the white aside. Mix yolks well, gradually adding the cream, milk, and sugar. Get back to the egg white - WHIP IT (whip it good!) until "soft peaks" form. Fold the white into the rest. Gradually add the alcohol. Either add nutmeg right away, or sprinkle on top later. AGE for at least 2 hours in refridgerator, uncovered.', NULL),
('Egg Nog Ice-Cream', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Allow ice-cream to soften. Mix all of the ingredients together and refrigerate. Serve with ground nutmeg sprinkled on top. Serve in a punch bowl or another big bowl', NULL),
('Egg Nog #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Beat yolks until light in color. Slowly add bourbon, cognac, while beating at slow speed. Chill 3 hrs. Add salt to whites, beat to peaks. Whip s cream until stiff. Fold whipped cream into yolk mixture, then fold in the beaten egg whites. Chill one hour. Serve with nutmeg sprinkled on top. For thinner mixture add 1 or 2 cups of milk. Serve in a punch bowl or another big bowl.', NULL),
('Egg Nog #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Separate 6 eggs. Beat yolks well. Beat in 1/2 cup sugar. Clean/degrease beaters and bowl. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Beat in 1/2 cup sugar. Fold in yolks to whites. Gently stir in 1 pt heavy cream, 1 pt milk, 1 pt bourbon, and 1 oz rum. Serve as is or well chilled. Double recipe to fill a punch bowl.', NULL),
('Egg Nog #3', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Separate eggs and refrigerate the whites. Beat ylks until light in color. Gradually beat in sugar, then slowly beat in 1 cup of rum. Let stand covered for atleast 1 hr. Add rest of liquor, cream, and peack brandy, beating constantly. Refrigerate, covered, for 3 hours. Beat egg whites until stiff, fold in. Serve sprinkled with nutmeg. Serve in a punch bowl or another medium sized bowl.', NULL),
('Egg Nog #5', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In an electric mixer, beat the egg yolks with the sugar until thick and lemon colored. Slowly add the bourbon and cognac, while beating at a slow speed. Chill several hours. Add the salt to the egg whites and beat until almost stiff, or until the beaten whites form a peak that bends slightly. Whip the cream until stiff. Fold the whipped cream intothe yolk mixture, then fold in the beaten egg white', NULL),
('Eggnog - Spiked', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Separate the eggs. In an electric mixer, beat the egg yolks with the sugar until thick and lemon colored. Slowly add the bourbon and cognac, while beating at slow speed. Chill several hours. Add the salt to the egg whites and beat until almost stiff, or until the beaten whites form a peak that bends slightly. Whip the cream until stiff. Fold the whipped cream into the yolk mixture, then fold in th', NULL),
('Eggnog - "Kentucky-style"', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Separate eggs. Beat yolks, add sugar. Add bourbon slowly while beating. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold whites into egg yolk mixture, then fold whipped cream into mixture. Refrigerate for more than 4 days. Stir frequently to avoid separation. Color will change to a pale Serve with nutmeg or cinnamon.', NULL),
('Ginger Syllabub', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Put the sherry, sugar, spices, and lemon juice into a large mixing bowl. Stir until well-blended, then leave to soak for at least half an hour. Beat the cream until it is stiff. Fold in the chopped ginger. Chill thoroughly. Before serving divide into four serving bowls and top with crumbs of crystallized ginger and a shake of nutmeg.', NULL),
('Glogg Extract', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Of course in Norway most people just buy an extract. Anyway, this makes a pretty nice Glogg: Add cloves, cardamon pods, cinnamon, and citrus peel to a glass with a generous measure of snaps (akvavit) or vodka. Let sit for a day or so. This makes a cery nice extract that can be added to any decent red wine. Just heat up the wine slowly (dont let it boil!!), and add sugar and extract to taste.', NULL),
('Glogg #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all the non-alcoholic ingredients in a heavy enamel or stainless steel saucepan, bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Add the red wine and the port and bring to a boil again. Remove from heat and let steep, covered, for at least 2 hours. Then bring back to a simmer, add the brandy, and heat for 1 minute. If you want to be fancy you can put it into a warmed metal bowl, turn down the lights', NULL),
('Glogg - Christmas', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Stir half a bottle of the wine with the spicesand sugar under heating, close to boiling. Remove casserolee from heat. Set aside for 24 hours. Strain off spices, and add remaining wine, vodka, and sherry. Add appx. 10 dashed aromatic tincture (this is a spice concentrate). Bottle your glogg, seal well, and let mature for a week. Mix with red wine or water, heat and serve in irish coffee cup.', NULL),
('Glogg - Swedish', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Put cardamon seeds, cinnamon, cloves and orange parts in nylon bag and tie top. In large saucepan put bag, half bottle of the wine, and the raisins. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Add remaining wine and the almond, heat through. In another saucepan warm about 1/3 of the brandy (or aquavit), pour in sugar and light with match to flame. When sugar has melted, pour in the remainder of brandy. If ne', NULL),
('Great Pumpkin Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Serve in a hollowed out pumpkin with floating pumpkin chunks.', NULL),
('Hop Skip and Go Naked Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Take a Cooler and throw a bag of ice in it. Add beer, white liquor and frozen Lemon-Lime Daqueri mix. Stir until Daqueri mix has liquified. Enjoy.', NULL),
('Hot Devilish Daiquiri', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In 2 qt. microproof casserole, combine hot water, sugar, spices, and concentrated juices. Stir, then cook on HI 5-6 minutes or until mixture boils. Heat rum in microproof container on HI for 30 seconds. Ignite and pour over hot beverage. Ladle into punch cups for serving.', NULL),
('Hot-Buttered Rum', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In a mug put sugar, butter, rum and cloves. Fill with boiling water. Stir.', NULL),
('Jamaica Me Crazy', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Fill a tall glass with ice. Pour in rum and tia maria. Add pineapple juice.', NULL),
('Sud-Ouest', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Shake and strain. Add a few drops of grenadine. Garnish with a slice of lime, a maraschino cherry and fresh mint.', NULL),
('Light Sangria with Pineapple', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In a pitcher, dissolve the sugar in the apple juice. Add lemon juice, wine, pineapple and apple in chunks. Mix. Add ginger ale and ice right before serving.', NULL),
('Monarchy Luau Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Remove rind and core form pineapple, coarsely chop fruit. Combine pineapple, brandy and sugar, marinate 6 hours or overnight. Pour pineapple juice into a ring mold and freeze. Add wine to pineapple-brandy mixture, refrigerate 30 minutes. Add pineapple juice ring and champagne just before serving.', NULL),
('Mulled Wine', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Simmer 3 cups water with, sugar, cloves, cinnamon sticks, and lemon peel in a stainless steel pot for 10 minutes. Add wine heat to a "coffee temperature" (DO NOT BOIL) then add the brandy.', NULL),
('Null & Void Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix with ice in a Tupperware dish pan. Serve in 16 oz glasses (with caution). Tastes great, but can lead to wastedness if comsumed too quickly, hence the name NULL & VOID punch.', NULL),
('Old Fashioned Hot Buttered Rum', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In 2-quart suacepan combine sugar, brown sugar and butter. Cook over low hear, stirring occasionally, until butter is melted (6-8 min). In large mixing bowl, combine cooked mixture with ice-cream, beat at medium speed, scraping bowl often until smooth (1-2 min). Store refrigerated up to 2 weeks or frozen up to one month. For each serving, fill mug with 1/4 cup mixture, 1 oz. rum and 3/4 cup boilin', NULL),
('Party Slush Punch #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix ingredients together, freeze to slush consistency and serve "slushy".', NULL),
('Party Slush Punch #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Put the ingredients into a container in the freezer (stir occasionally while freezing). To serve: put 2/3 slush to 1/3 7-up in each glass or same ratio in punch bowl.', NULL),
('Party Slush Punch #3', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix the following ingredients together and freeze. When slushy, drink as is or mix with 7-UP.', NULL),
('Pineapple Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Put the pineapple pieces in a punch bowl and pour the sherry over them. Chill for 2 hours. Put tea and sugar in a pot, add red wine, lemon juice and rum. Heat but do not boil the mixture. Pour over the pineapple pieces.', NULL),
('Ponche de Pina', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Peel pineapples, chop or shread. Add water and let stand overnight. Put in large saucepan with spices, sugar, and coconut milk. Boil for 5 minutes. Strain liquid into large pitcher. Add rum and serve hot.', NULL),
('Porch Crawlers', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.', NULL),
('Purple Jesus', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.', NULL),
('Raspberry Cordial', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all ingredients and stir until sugar is disolved. Store in large bottles for 22 days, then put in gift bottles and seal.', NULL),
('Sangria #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix all together in a pitcher and refrigerate. Add cloves and cinnamon sticks to taste. Serve in wine glasses.', NULL),
('Sangria #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Peel the apples and cut into small cubes. Peel the oranges, take out the pips, and cut into small cubes. Warm the orange juice, the sugar and the mandarin peels until the sugar dissolves. Mix all the ingredients in a pitcher, except the ice and the soda which you add just before serving. Serve in wine glsses.', NULL),
('Sweet Sangria', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Dissolve the sugar in hot water and cool. Peel the citrus fruits and break into wedges. Mix the wine, sugar syrup, fruit, and Fresca in a pitcher and put in the fridge for a few hours. Serve in tall glasses with a straw.', NULL),
('Sauterne', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix the cognac and curacao several hours ahead of time. When ready to serve, pour the necessary amount of this mixture over a block of ice or ice mold in a *cold* punch bowl, and add *thoroughly chilled* champagne. Stir and serve at once, WITHOUT LADLING BACK AND FORTH OVER THE ICE, as this will eliminate the bubbles.', NULL),
('Strawberry Bolle', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Sprinkle strawbs with sugar, add one bottle cider. Chill for several hours. To serve, pour into large bowl with ice, add the rest of the wine. Serve in small wine glasses.', NULL),
('Syllabub', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine wine, lemon rind, and juice. Stir in 1 cup of the sugar and let stand until sugar dissolves. Combine milk and cream, add wine mixture, and beat with a rotary beater until frothy. Beat egg whites until stiff, add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, a little at a time, beating constantly until whites stand in peaks. Pour wine mixture into punch bowl, top with puffs of egg white, and sprinkle whites wit', NULL),
('Tom and Jerry Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Beat egg whites to a stiff froth. Separately beat egg yolks until light in color, gradually add the powdered sugar and spices. Fold yolk mixture into whites. Divide mixture between four 8 oz. mugs. Add 1/2 shot brandy and 1 shot rum to each mug, fill with hot beverage. Stir well and top with nutmeg.', NULL),
('Truck Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Give yourself a break, use ice.', NULL),
('Wassail #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Simmer the nonalcoholic ingredients together for 1-2 hours, then add the wine and rum about 10 minutes before serving (hot).', NULL),
('Wine Punch', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Combine all of the ingredients and pour over a block of ice.', NULL),
('Margarita', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Rub rim of cocktail glass with lime juice, dip rim in salt. Shake all ingredients with ice, strain into the salt-rimmed glass, and serve.', NULL),
('Polarbear #1', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Take one part vodka into the glass, pour one part lime in the same glass. Then you take two parts of 7-up or sprite. Mix this together with a straw or something like that. Ice is recommended.', NULL),
('Izayoi', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In a shaker half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Shake well. Strain into a cocktail glass, and serve. (Name mean: 16th moon in Japanese)', NULL),
('Brave Bull Shooter', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'Pour Tabasco into bottom of shot glass and fill with tequila.', NULL),
('Fahrenheit 5000', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'Cover bottom of shot glass with Tabasco Sauce and then fill with half Firewater and half Absolut Peppar.', NULL),
('Popped cherry', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Served over ice in a tall glass with a popped cherry (can add more popped cherries if in the mood)!', NULL),
('The Incredible Hulk', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Add 2 oz of Captain Morgan to glass. Add sugar. Add Mountain Dew till mix turns green.', NULL),
('Alabama Riot', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Pour fruit punch and ice into a glass, add southern comfort, peppermint schnapps and vodka. Stir. Finish with lime juice.', NULL),
('Reggae Ambassador', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Fill a blender 1/2 full (or 1/2 empty) with ice. Fill 1/4 of the blender with vodka. Fill 1/2 with pine-orange-banana fruit juice. Fill the rest with fresh strawberries, and about 4 tsp. sugar. Blend, serve with an orange slice.', NULL),
('Mind Eraser', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'In a rocks glass pour vodka, the Kahlua and then the tonic water. Serve with a straw.', NULL),
('Pamela', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Simply make a standard vodka and tonic and garnish liberally with sliced cucumbers. sounds funny, but makes a great hot weather drink.', NULL),
('Atomic Lokade', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In a shaker, place lemonade, vodka, blue Curacao, and triple sec together. Shake with ice and strain into glass. Add sugar to taste', NULL),
('Mexican Mouthwash', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'Pour into shaker chill, and gently swirl together.', NULL),
('Pecker Head', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'In a strainer add all three ingredients. Fill half full of ice. Shake well. Strain into a double shot glass.', NULL),
('Colorado Bulldog', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In a shaker mix Vodka, Kahlua, and milk. Pour into a rocks glass and add a splash of Coca-Cola', NULL),
('Carribean pineapple', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix in a lowball glass and serve over ice', NULL),
('Bullfrog', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Shake well (preferably in a closed container). Stir (preferably with a spoon in an opened container)', NULL),
('Cucaracha', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'In a low glass put Tequila first, than Kahlua. Flame the coktail. Two people had to drink in the same glass with two plastic-pipe. The goal is to drink before the plastic-pipe melt down.', NULL),
('Hillinator', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix the Captain Morgan, Mountain Dew, and sugar in one class. Pour the fire water into a shot glass. Take the shot, then follow it with the mixed drink. Make sure to drink the mixed drink quickly', NULL),
('Tequila Mockingbird', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Fill tall rocks glass or tumbler with ice. Add tequila and triple sec, followed by O.J. and cranberry. Add blue curacao. DO NOT MIX. Garnish with lemon or cherry if desired.', NULL),
('Green Lantern', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix all together in order, shake once and pour into glass.', NULL),
('Irish Coffee #2', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Mix cofee and chilled Irish Cream and half & half. Add sugar and stir. Serve hot in an Irish coffee cup.', NULL),
('B-52 #1', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'Layer the Kahlua, Amaretto, and Irish Cream into a shot glass in that order. After drinking, notice the Vapor Trails.', NULL),
('Wahoo', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Over ice add 151 and amaretto. Top off with pineapple juice.', NULL),
('911', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'Mix equal proprtions of each in one shot glass.', NULL),
('Chocolate Paradise', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Simply pour over ice into a tall glass.', NULL),
('Malibu juice', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Put 3 shots of the rum in a glass, fill the rest of the cup with the juice.', NULL),
('Russian Roulette', 0, 0, 'Shot', 'Fill two or more shooter 1 oz. shooter glasses with the kahlua and vodka and place a slice of orange on the top of each glass. Put the Sambuca in a wine glass and light. Pour the lit Sambuca on the shooters below and let burn for a short time in front of your bedazzled guests. Blow out the fire and instruct the drinkers of the shooters to drink out of the glass first and chew the Sambuca-soaked or', NULL),
('Diesel', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Pour the lager first then add the blackcurrant cordial. Top up with the cider. The colour sholud be very dark approaching the colour of Guiness.', NULL),
('Reptile', 0, 0, 'Mixed Drink', 'Make sure all ingredients are chilled. Add in order: ET, OJ, Dew. Stir lightly. Like most OJ drinks, the alcohol is hard to taste. A padded bar is recomended.', NULL),
